🚀 2. CUTOVER DAY RUNBOOK (REAL COMMANDS)

This is the most critical part.

⸻

🔹 STEP 0: Pre-checks

# Check DB replication lag
SELECT * FROM pg_stat_replication;

# RabbitMQ queue depth
rabbitmqctl list_queues name messages_ready messages_unacknowledged


⸻

🔹 STEP 1: Freeze Producers

kubectl scale deployment producer --replicas=0


⸻

🔹 STEP 2: Drain Queues

watch rabbitmqctl list_queues

👉 Wait until:
	•	messages_ready = 0
	•	messages_unacknowledged = 0

⸻

🔹 STEP 3: Final DB Sync

SELECT pg_switch_wal();

👉 Ensure replication caught up

⸻

🔹 STEP 4: Switch Config (AWS)

Update Helm values:

DB_HOST: rds-endpoint
MQ_HOST: aws-mq-endpoint

Deploy via Argo CD

⸻

🔹 STEP 5: Enable AWS Consumers

kubectl scale deployment consumer --replicas=3


⸻

🔹 STEP 6: Shift Traffic

Option A (DNS)
	•	Update Route53 → point to AWS ALB

Option B (Gradual)
	•	10% → 50% → 100%

⸻

🔹 STEP 7: Monitor (FIRST 30 MINUTES CRITICAL)

Check:

kubectl logs -f deployment/service-a


⸻

🔙 3. ROLLBACK COMMANDS (IF THINGS GO WRONG)

⸻

🔹 Immediate rollback

# Stop AWS consumers
kubectl scale deployment consumer --replicas=0

# Resume ON-PREM
kubectl scale deployment producer --replicas=3


⸻

🔹 Switch DNS back
	•	Route53 → ON-PREM IP

⸻

🔹 Resume ON-PREM MQ

👉 Remove federation temporarily if needed

⸻

🧯 4. TROUBLESHOOTING PLAYBOOK (REAL ISSUES)

⸻

❌ Issue 1: Duplicate Messages

Cause:
	•	Federation + replay

Fix:

if message_id in processed:
    skip()


⸻

❌ Issue 2: DB Replication Lag

Check:

SELECT now() - pg_last_xact_replay_timestamp();

Fix:
	•	Delay cutover
	•	Increase instance size

⸻

❌ Issue 3: Service Latency High

Causes:
	•	Network latency (VPN)
	•	DB in AWS, app still on-prem

Fix:
	•	Move dependent services together

⸻

❌ Issue 4: Hidden Dependency Failure

Example:
	•	Service A calls internal API B (still on-prem)

Fix:
	•	Map all dependencies before migration

⸻

❌ Issue 5: RabbitMQ Ordering Issues

Fix:
	•	Use single queue per partition
	•	Avoid parallel consumers if strict ordering needed

⸻

📊 5. MONITORING DASHBOARD (WHAT TO TRACK)

⸻

MUST metrics:
	•	API latency
	•	Error rate
	•	DB connections
	•	MQ queue depth
	•	Replication lag

⸻

🧠 6. RESUME / INTERVIEW STORY (STRONG VERSION)

⸻

🔹 Short Version

“I led migration of 15+ critical stateful services from on-prem Kubernetes to AWS using a zero-downtime strategy.
	•	Used Amazon EKS for container orchestration
	•	Migrated databases to Amazon RDS for PostgreSQL with logical replication
	•	Implemented RabbitMQ federation to Amazon MQ
	•	Used Argo CD for GitOps deployment
	•	Ran systems in parallel with validation to ensure data consistency

This achieved zero downtime and no data loss.”

⸻

🔹 Strong Version (Senior Level)

“I designed a hybrid migration architecture using shadow deployments and parallel processing.

Key challenges:
	•	Maintaining transaction integrity
	•	Preventing message duplication
	•	Ensuring rollback safety

Solutions:
	•	Built a reconciliation system for data validation
	•	Implemented idempotent consumers
	•	Used phased cutover with controlled traffic shifting

This reduced migration risk and ensured compliance with financial-grade reliability requirements.”

